  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (9dcc095 2022-06-28T00:03:46.153858156Z\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge coverage\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nThe optimizer settings I have in my `foundry.toml` appear to be ignored by the coverage command.\r\n\r\nI think this is the case (haven't lookend into code) since my project compiles perfectly with `forge build` etc, but gets stack to deep issues when I run `forge coverage` (ie I haven't been able to test coverage yet :crying_cat_face: ). When I remove the optimizer from the config I get the error at the exact same stack to deep error in the same place.\r\n\r\nThe command line arguments for the optimiser are also not helping. eg `forge coverage --optimize --optimizer-runs 1000`.",
